{"timestamp":"2026-04-13T08:36:37.732Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"1. Medium: `pkg/gitsync` leaks internal engine vocabulary directly into the public API, which freezes unstable implementation details as API contract. `RefMapping` is a direct alias of `internal/validation.RefMapping`, `RefKind`/`Action` constants are sourced from `internal/planner`, and result fields like `RelayMode`, `RelayReason`, `TempRefs`, and `BootstrapSuggested` are passed through verbatim from `internal/syncer`. That makes the first public cut brittle against internal refactors rather than establishing its own stable boundary. [pkg/gitsync/types.go:35](\\/Users\\/soph\\/Work\\/entire\\/devenv\\/git-sync\\/pkg\\/gitsync\\/types.go:35) [pkg/gitsync/types.go:88](\\/Users\\/soph\\/Work\\/entire\\/devenv\\/git-sync\\/pkg\\/gitsync\\/types.go:88) [pkg/gitsync/types.go:163](\\/Users\\/soph\\/Work\\/entire\\/devenv\\/git-sync\\/pkg\\/gitsync\\/types.go:163)\n\n2. Medium: `PlanResult` is just an alias of `SyncResult`, so the public dry-run API inherits execution-only fields whose semantics are at best incidental and at worst misleading for a plan call. Fields like `Pushed`, `Deleted`, `Relay`, `BatchCount`, and `TempRefs` are not really “plan” concepts, but they are now part of the public planning surface and will constrain future cleanup. [pkg/gitsync/types.go:163](\\/Users\\/soph\\/Work\\/entire\\/devenv\\/git-sync\\/pkg\\/gitsync\\/types.go:163) [pkg/gitsync/types.go:184](\\/Users\\/soph\\/Work\\/entire\\/devenv\\/git-sync\\/pkg\\/gitsync\\/types.go:184) [pkg/gitsync/client.go:34](\\/Users\\/soph\\/Work\\/entire\\/devenv\\/git-sync\\/pkg\\/gitsync\\/client.go:34)\n\n3. Low: Public request validation is too thin for a first exported package. `Validate` only checks URL presence, so invalid protocol values, conflicting/invalid mappings, and other malformed inputs are accepted by the public layer and only fail later inside `internal/syncer`. That is not a translati